title: Grateful Dead Live at Autzen Stadium, U. of Oregon on 1990-06-23
lineage: Sony PCM-2600(Apogee AES/EBU)>Sound Devices 722 (16/48)>Firewire>Macbook>Sound Studio 3.6(fades, normalize peak, +gain, track)>Wave Editor 1.5.7 (iZotope Resampler)>xACT 2.21(align on sector boundaries, encode, tag, fingerprint)>flac16 (level 8 ); DAT clone (2) provided by: Craig Hillwig; Transferred and seeded by: Lenny Stubbe
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger-> West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle, Cumberland Blues, Far From Me, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Promised Land

Set 2

Eyes Of The World, Looks Like Rain-> Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: bass is a little overwhelming I usually head first for the schoeps, especially one prepared by Chillwig and Stubbe.  Unfortunately this tape has bass so extreme it actually is hard to listen to on my home stereo.  YMMV
